 context.Framed by an important introduction by anthropologist Sherry B. Ortner, the articles cover such topics as seventeenth-century English ghosts, Jewish merchants in early capitalism, Egyptian women in the age of television, and the role of Sherpas in Himalayan mountaineering, as well as such methodological issues as the place of emotional empathy and "complicity" in ethnographic fieldwork, and the mutual illumination of culture and history.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aAnthropology. 4aGeneral. 4aSocial Science. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh1 aAbu-Lughod, Lila, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreenblatt, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarcus, George E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrtner, Sherry B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrtner, Sherry B., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRosaldo, Renato I., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSewell, William H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZemon Davis, Natalie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052021601340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052035423440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520354234423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520354234/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles